(1) Any person who— (a) fails to give information or produce books, accounts or other documents when required to do so under the provisions of section nine; (b) with intent to evade the provisions of this Act, destroys, mutilates, defaces, secretes or removes any books, accounts or other documents; (c) obstructs any person lawfully performing any functions under this Act; shall be guilty of an offence and liable on conviction to a fine not exceeding fifteen thousand penalty units or to imprisonment for a period not exceeding two years, or to both.
